     <h2>
      <a href="http://www.appstate.edu/">
       Appalachian State University
      </a>
     </h2>
     <h1>
      <a href="/">
       Office of the Controller
      </a>
     </h1>
    </div>
   </div>
   <div id="content">
    <div class="guts">
     <div class="two02col" style="float: right; width: 740px;">
      <div id="content-main">
       <div id="attachedimage">
       </div>
       <div id="content_float_right">
       </div>
       <div class="node odd full-node node-type-page" id="node-2">
        <div class="node-inner">
         <div class="content">
          <p>
           The Controller's Office is a division of Business Affairs and consists of four separate functional areas;
           <a href="/accounting-data-control">
            Accounting/Data Control
           </a>
           ,
           <a href="http://payroll.appstate.edu/">
            Payroll
           </a>
           ,
           <a href="http://studentaccounts.appstate.edu/">
            Treasury Services and Student Accounts
           </a>
           , and
           <a href="/special-funds">
            Special Funds
           </a>
           . The Controller's Office is located in the Business Affairs Annex at 251B Industrial Park Drive. Special Funds and General Accounting are located on the first floor and Payroll and additional Controller's Office staff are located on the second floor. Student Accounts and Treasury Services office is located on the second floor of John E. Thomas Hall.
          </p>
          <h3>
           <strong>
            Mission:
           </strong>
          </h3>
          <p>
           The mission of the Controller's Office is to provide accountability for University resources and appropriate dissemination of financial information to maximize the use of University resources in compliance with Federal and State legislation, Federal and State policies and procedures, Board of Governors policies and procedures, Appalachian State University policies and procedures, and requirements of external funding sources.
           <span style="font-size: 1.17em;">
           </span>
          </p>
          <h3>
           <strong>
            Ethics and Professional Conduct:
           </strong>
          </h3>
          <p>
           <strong>
            The Controller's Office is committed to maintaining the highest standards of Professional Ethics.
           </strong>
          </p>
          <p>
           <a href="/sites/controller.appstate.edu/files/Code_of_Ethics-ASU%20CO.pdf">
            Click Here to view the Controller's Office code of Professional Conduct
           </a>
          </p>
          <p>
           <a href="/sites/controller.appstate.edu/files/NC%20BOE%20Vol%205%20Is%206.pdf">
            N.C. Board of Ethics Vol. 5 Issue 6 "Gifts and Freebies"
           </a>
          </p>
          <p>
           <a href="/sites/controller.appstate.edu/files/ExecutiveOrder24GiftBan%20(1).pdf">
            Executive Order No. 24: Gifts to State Employees
           </a>
          </p>
          <p>
          </p>
          <p>
           For more information, please
           <a href="http://controller.appstate.edu/contact-information-0">
            contact us
           </a>
           .
          </p>
         </div>
         <div class="meta">
